 THE late award-winning producer, Robbie Malinga, may be gone
but his family and fans still remembers him. Earlier today, his widow, Ann Malinga, took time off to wish
the late star a 50th birthday. Ann wrote on her Instagram page that the late star would
have turned 50 today. She wrote a short and sweet message that read: “On this day
50 years ago. This legend was born.” She added, “Happy heavenly 50th birthday”, to the message. Robbie passed away after a short illness in 2017. He gave music lovers smash hits including Lilizela Mzansi
and Baby Please, among others. He also collaborated with many local artists.   and Vusi Nova.